<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Index</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/header_footer.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/4.7.0/css/font-awesome.min.css"/>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/index.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <div id="header_div">
            <span id="fakelos">Fakelos</span>
            <% if (name != null) { %>
                <span id="user_name">Hello, <%= name %></span>
                <form action="/logout?_method=DELETE" method="POST" id="logout_form">
                    <button id="logout_button" type="submit">Log Out</button>
                </form>
            <% }else{ %>
                <a href="/register" class="acc_buttons">Register</a>
                <a href="/login" class="acc_buttons">Login</a>
            <% } %>
            <div class="cart"><a href="/cart"><img src="imgs/cart.png"></a></div>
        </div>  
        <ul class="nav_bar">
            <a class="nav_ref" href="/">Home</a>    
            <div class="search">
                <input type="text" minlength="3" autocomplete="off" id="search_value"><br>
                <button id="search_button" onclick="search_function()"><img src="imgs/search.png"></button>
            </div>   
            <a class="nav_ref" href="/contact">Contact Us</a>      
        </ul> 
    </header>
    <div id="content">
        <label>Product Categories</label>
        <label id="access_categories" hidden><%= JSON.stringify(main_cat_table) %></label>
        <ul id="categories_ul">

        </ul>
        <label id="website_info">Info about the current and future state of the website.</label>
        <div class="contains">
            <p>This project website, works on a Nodejs Express server.</p>
            <p>Registered Users are saved in a MongoDB database with encrypted passwords. When they try to login, the server checks the db for the email given,if it exists
                and the password now temporarily decrypted is equal to the password given in the login form then the user logins successfully.
            </p>
            <p>Every item shown in this website was fetched from the Fake Store Api previously. Now approximately 60 products are stored in MongoDB.</p>
            <p>The search functionality returns every product that has the searched term in the title.</p>
            <p>The Contact form works as expected, saves every customer message in a MongoDB table and redirects the user to the home page.
            </p>
            <p>The related products,are consisted of 3 random products from the same sub category(mobile phones,laptops, men fashion etc).</p>
            <p>The customer can only add items to the cart if he is logged in.</p>
            <p>When the customer adds a product in their cart, the 'cart' field in the MongoDB table is updated. The 'cart' field is an array consisting
                of json objects {product_id,count}. So whenever a product is added to the cart, the product id and the number of items is pushed in the array.
            </p>
            <p>When the customer deletes an item from the cart, the table in MongoDB is updated and then the customer is redirected to the Cart page with the product removed.</p>
            <p>When a customer is logged in, he can leave a review in any product and other users can see them.</p>
            <p>Proper filters in the storage view. Products can be sorted by price ascending/descending, rating ascending/descending and popularity(fake review count). 
                The user can choose a manufacturer in the filters and only products from that manufacturer are shown. Finally, the user can choose a minimum price and only products
                with price greater than that min value are shown.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="future">
            <label>Will be added in the future:</label>
            <p>The website will undergo a lot of design changes.</p>
            <p>Advaned Search functionality.</p>
            <p>The server will send an email to the customer that filled the contact form to reaffirm them of the arrival of their message.</p>
            <p>Proper register form, that checks if the customer already exists or if the email already exists.</p>
            <p>Account settings.</p>
            <p>More pages with different stuff.</p>
        </div>

    </div>
    <footer class="footer">
        <div id="upper_footer">
            <div class="who">
                <label>Who Am I</label>
                <p>I am a senior student at the University of Macedonia on the apartment of Applied Informatics.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="offer">
                <label>What Can I Offer(with reasonable scale)</label>
                <ul>
                    <li><p>Web Development and Design</p></li>
                    <li><p>Software Development and Design</p></li>
                    <li><p>Game Development and Design</p></li>
                    <li><p>Absolutely Everything</p></li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div id="contact_socials">
                <a id="contact" href="/contact">Contact Me</a>
                <ul class="socials">
                    <li><a href="#"><i class="fa fa-facebook"></i></a></li>
                    <li><a href="#"><i class="fa fa-twitter"></i></a></li>
                    <li><a href="#"><i class="fa fa-instagram"></i></a></li>
                    <li><a href="#"><i class="fa fa-youtube"></i></a></li>
                </ul>

            </div>
        </div>
        <div id="copyright">
            <p>Copyright &copy fakelos</p>
        </div>

    </footer>
    <script src="js/home.js"></script>  
</body>
</html>
